comments.text: I guess they were unalived, and the villagers surely know who did it, but they keep their mouths shut. Also, isn't it weird that the backpack showed up when there was a  reward announced?

comments.text:
Not all of this is accurate. The report showed metatarsal fractures in her foot (top bones)indicating either a fall or repeated stress. Some evidence showed early healing, suggesting she may have survived for a short time after the injury.

Periostitis (inflammation of tissue around the tibia) attributed to repetitive use before the incident. 

A rolled-up ball of skin found in August (nearly five months later) still had maggots and showed little decomposition. Investigators speculated it may have been stored in cooler/darker conditions before being depositedraising suspicions of tampering.
comments.author: @VoiceForTheSilenced
